## Commands We Used (Key Steps)

### A) Install/replace Origin cert & key

```bash
sudo nano /etc/nginx/ssl/garimela-origin.pem
sudo nano /etc/nginx/ssl/garimela-origin.key
sudo chmod 600 /etc/nginx/ssl/garimela-origin.key
```

### B) Copy to CloudPanel SNI path

```bash
sudo cp /etc/nginx/ssl/garimela-origin.pem /etc/nginx/ssl-certificates/garimela.com.crt
sudo cp /etc/nginx/ssl/garimela-origin.key /etc/nginx/ssl-certificates/garimela.com.key

sudo cp /etc/nginx/ssl/garimela-origin.pem /etc/nginx/ssl-certificates/admin.garimela.com.crt
sudo cp /etc/nginx/ssl/garimela-origin.key /etc/nginx/ssl-certificates/admin.garimela.com.key

sudo chmod 600 /etc/nginx/ssl-certificates/garimela.com.key /etc/nginx/ssl-certificates/admin.garimela.com.key
```

### C) Fix missing php snippet

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /etc/nginx/snippets

sudo tee /etc/nginx/snippets/fastcgi-php.conf > /dev/null <<'EOF'
fastcgi_split_path_info ^(.+\.php)(/.+)$;
include fastcgi_params;
fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME $document_root$fastcgi_script_name;
fastcgi_param PATH_INFO $fastcgi_path_info;
EOF
```

### D) Validate + reload (no restart)

```bash
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

### E) Verify origin cert is correct (SNI)

```bash
echo | openssl s_client -connect 127.0.0.1:443 -servername garimela.com 2>/dev/null | openssl x509 -noout -subject -ext subjectAltName
echo | openssl s_client -connect 127.0.0.1:443 -servername admin.garimela.com 2>/dev/null | openssl x509 -noout -subject -ext subjectAltName
```

### F) Check origin cert expiry (2041 expected)

```bash
openssl x509 -in /etc/nginx/ssl/garimela-origin.pem -noout -dates
echo | openssl s_client -connect 127.0.0.1:443 -servername garimela.com 2>/dev/null | openssl x509 -noout -dates
```

### G) Confirm Strict path from server side (Cloudflare)

```bash
curl -I https://garimela.com
curl -I https://admin.garimela.com
```

### H) Remove unused api vhost

```bash
sudo rm -f /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/api.garimela.com.conf
sudo nginx -t && sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

### I) Confirm no warnings

```bash
sudo nginx -t 2>&1 | grep -i warn || echo "No warnings ✅"
```

